originalText.text:
I have been looking for an online business checking account for a while.  And I received the Kabbage information because I am a American Express customer.  It was easy to open the account.  It is a great product, but…

1) It is very difficult to set up direct deposit to receive fund.  It provides only your account number and routing.  I have to google the bank address and phone number (I found out it is green dot bank).  It was confusing.  I am able to set up most of that but some will not accept the information.

2) Mobile deposit -  it takes a few business days to get the deposits into your account (many banks do this almost instantly);

3) The phone app is horrible.  I could not use my iPhone fingerprint to open.  I have to use my AM Exp credential to sign in.

4) The account indicates my link bank accounts have problems but in fact there is none;

5)  A few days ago, I logged into my account and found out it has been locked.  I called a rep, and he could not unlocked.  Then he created a ticket.  I just logged into and it is still locked after a few business day.  No access to my fund and could not use my debit card.

